The paper deals with image processing and computer vision techniques for remote sensing data, which suggests that it could belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The use of a generative adversarial network (GAN) also suggests that it could belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves the design of a fusion architecture and the use of a fully convolutional network, which could suggest it belongs to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The use of remote sensing data could also suggest it belongs to the graphics (cs.GR) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves the use of image processing techniques, which could suggest it belongs to the information theory (cs.IT) sub-category.
